metadata.name: Coronado #26
metadata.description:
This series is about the beauty and charm of imperfection, chaos amidst order, and letting go. It's about knowing that however much control we think we may have, things can all fall apart or burst into something unexpectedly wonderful at any moment, even without our hands tightly on the reigns.

Please see fxtext article linked from main project page for more background on the project and rendering notes.

Some key commands in live mode:

G : Toggle grain
S : Save current resolution
1 : 4000x5000
2 : 6000x7500
3 : 8000x10000
4 : 10000x12500
5 : 12000x15000
6 : 14000x17500
(1-6 work best on Chrome)
(rendering takes longer as resolution increases)

metadata.name: Millefoglie #411
metadata.description:
"A mille-feuille (French pronunciation: ​[mil fœj], "thousand-sheets"), also known by the names Napoleon, vanilla slice, and custard slice, is a dessert made of puff pastry layered with pastry cream. Its modern form was influenced by improvements made by Marie-Antoine Carême.

Traditionally, a mille-feuille is made up of three layers of puff pastry (pâte feuilletée), alternating with two layers of pastry cream (crème pâtissière). The top pastry layer is finished in various ways: sometimes it is topped with whipped cream, or it may be dusted with icing sugar, cocoa, pastry crumbs, or sliced almonds. It may also be glazed with icing or fondant alone, or in alternating white (icing) and brown (chocolate) or other colored icing stripes, and combed to create a marbled effect." — Wikipedia

Prints available upon request: prints@stefancontiero.com
Best enjoyed on browsers supporting Display-P3 color gamut.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

@stefan_contiero

metadata.name: Diyalebuka #62
metadata.description:
Diyalebuka - "Thank you"! 

With this piece I hope to express my thanks and joy for being alive and able to create art. I hope the patterns and textures will bring you joy.

This piece is inspired by the patterns of the Ndebele of Southern Africa and the First Nations Salish of Vancouver Island.

* There are over 100 palettes arranged into 6 distinct families
* There can be between 2 and 10 bars

(The artwork will fit your available window and may take a while to generate if it's a larger resolution)

metadata.name: Ammophila dream #70
metadata.description:
I met an old man at the bar in a pub in Ireland. As it usually happens after a few pints of Guinness we started talking. 

He said how he spent his entire working life on an ocean-going ship, was in danger many times due to storms, and how he couldn't wait to retire and firmly set foot on land, finally spending time with his family, especially grandchildren. 

And that now as an old man, he is happiest on summer evenings, when the full moon lights up everything, he lies out on the grassy part of the beach and looks at the sea through the grass. I asked him why through the grass? He said - "I can't live without the sea, and looking at it through the grass is solid proof that I'm really on land after so many years, and that I'm not dreaming after all." 

This work is a dedication to that old man. I recently found out from my Irish friends that he died few months ago at age of 87. His ashes were scattered on the grassy part of the beach. Now he is forever close to his sea, but still firmly on land, which he has been striving for for years.

Sláinte mr. Doyle.

Made in p5.js
Bajiru, November 2022.

metadata.name: Canevach #120
metadata.description:
Canevach started as a code golfing experiment, 280 characters of HTML, CSS and JavaScript producing pixelated patterns when copy-pasted in the address bar of a web browser.

The code has been adapted for the sake of entropy control and readability, but I tried to keep it as lean as possible to honour the code golfing spirit that initiated the project.

The artwork is generated by manipulating pixels directly through the Canvas API.

Colours are uniformly selected in RGB space, without any colour theory considerations. The only exception is for black, which is made more prominent by the way the algorithm is initiated.

Features
• Canvas size: 8x8 | 16x16 | 32x32 | 64x64 | 128x128
• Number of colours: 1 to 5

metadata.name: FairyCells #282
metadata.description:
FairyCells is a series created by a generative system, displaying shapes, between 1 and 10, made up of three different color palettes. 
Cells cannot cross each other, and are composed of a flat tint and/or a hatch system.

You can right-click to download an SVG file of the NFT or press « E » to export as png (3401x3401px)

Moreover, the digital version can exist as a physical piece.
Owning the NFT gives the right to order, in addition, a 30x30cm plotter drawing of it. More information about it here: https://nft.julienespagnon.fr/fairy-cells.
You can see some test examples plotted in the google form: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1FO3Umh49qmJApZAlQgZ46a2y421QYEWIW8r72nLrW4Q/edit

Work by Julien Espagnon - 2021/2022

metadata.description: "You take the blue pill... the story ends, you wake up in your bed and believe whatever you want to believe. You take the red pill... you stay in Wonderland, and I show you how deep the rabbit hole goes"

metadata.name: Stitched: Trauma #387
metadata.description:
"Every happy family is alike; every unhappy family is unhappy in its own way." -- Tolstoy

Stitched: trauma is based on the same code, and premise, as Stitched, with one twist: childhood trauma distorts experiences and events; some are wildly chaotic; others obsessively retrace a few curves. It is an experiment in combinatorial complexity: are two mints ever indistinguishable? 

The distortion has been carefully designed to allow a huge space of legibly distinct possibilities.

f: toggle between square format and stretch aspect ratio
1-6: set pixel density

metadata.name: Coastal Waves #102
metadata.description:
Further experimentation with algorithmic natural movement and shape.

Each Coastal Waves comes in a Day or Night mode, the waves are completely algorithmic and unique to each piece. The variables include color of the Sky, Sun, Moon, Water and Water Highlights, position and size of the Sun/Moon, Moon Phase (including eclipse), number of Birds, position and number of Colored Stars in the night sky.

metadata.name: f-emerald #313
metadata.description:
f-emerald generates unique ephemeral crystal-like structures that morph in space. each generation has a different shape, animation and colour palette. 

the crystals flicker with colours in the dark most of the time. there is, however, a 20% chance of obtaining a crystal on a bright background with a light colour palette and one out of ten structures is created in black and white.

metadata.name: R3B00T #8
metadata.description:
The variety of noises is infinite. If today, when we have perhaps a thousand different machines, we can distinguish a thousand different noises, 
tomorrow, as new machines multiply, we will be able to distinguish ten, twenty, or thirty thousand different noises, 
not merely in a simply imitative way, but to combine them according to our imagination.
- Luigi Russolo (The Art of Noises, 1916)

___

Generative visual, noise algorithm, organic pattern, inspired by compact disc format, transform in autonomous system, and made with code.

* Interactive feature :
- Place your mouse cursor to visual screen (canvas)
- Left click to spin the cd and play audio
- Right click to reset or back to original

* Every piece in this project have different unique audio. (All sounds created with modular synthesizer)

___
